TextBody:
Hi Saveetha,
 
Thank you for reaching out to Netwrix Technical Support.
What is the error message you are getting from the Bulk Import job?
 
Can you set the Bulk Import to Debug mode and send us the log so we can review it?
To put the job on Debug mode, right-click on the job and click Properties.
Under the General tab, you will see the Log Level. If it is not already on Debug, click the dropdown and select it.
 
If the job was already on Debug, right-click on it and click Explore Folder. Open the OUTPUT folder, and you will see the FSAA Bulk Import_Log.tsv, which you can upload to this ticket.
 
If the job was not on Debug, you must put it on Debug, and you would need to rerun the job to collect the log before sending it to us.
 
You can use the link below to schedule a meeting.
https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=bCjG7hlnUGn1kmkAOyua4FAUpbItIwYce3cKZfsg6Qs-Z&MeetingID=WRbKQOHoCnwlE1Jk_0dyfjh19uFDE_L8HNJSYRC7cMM-Z
 
Thanks,


Frantz Jean Baptiste

TextBody:
Hi Saveetha,

I reviewed the attached Bulk Import logs for both domains and here are the errors:

GLOBAL:

28/06/2024 23:06:04    INFO    SAJobEngine    TReportThread.ProcessReportGenerationTask()    "Generating 2-FSAA Bulk Import23.Permission Scan_GLOBAL_WIN_Bulk Import ...."    Permission Scan_GLOBAL_WIN_Bulk Import        19772    25688    33584
28/06/2024 23:06:04    INFO    Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.Reporting    SqlDataProvider..ctor    "Command timeout is set to: 86400"            19772    25688    33584
28/06/2024 23:06:04    INFO    Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.Reporting    Report.DeleteJobReport    "There are no files to delete."            19772    25688    33584
28/06/2024 23:06:05    ERROR    SAJobEngine    TReportThread.ProcessReportGenerationTask()    "Unexpected exception: The specified path, file name, or both are too long. The fully qualified file name must be less than 260 characters, and the directory name must be less than 248 characters"    Permission Scan_GLOBAL_WIN_Bulk Import        19772    25688    33584
28/06/2024 23:06:05    INFO    SAJobEngine    TReportThread.Execute    "<- Work done"    Permission Scan_GLOBAL_WIN_Bulk Import        19772    25688    33584
28/06/2024 23:06:05    INFO    SAJobEngine    TReportTaskExecute.ProcessReportTask    "Report generation and publishing task is done"    Permission Scan_GLOBAL_WIN_Bulk Import        44000    25688    33584
28/06/2024 23:06:05    ERROR    SAJobEngine    TReportTaskExecute.ProcessReportTask    "Report generation task failed."    Permission Scan_GLOBAL_WIN_Bulk Import        44000    25688    33584

NHY:

28/06/2024 23:05:09    ERROR    FILESYSTEMACCESS    Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.Tasks.Task.StartExecute    "code = Error (1), message = System.Data.SQLite.SQLiteException (0x800007BF): SQL logic error  unknown database StrucMap    

28/06/2024 23:05:29    ERROR    SAJobEngine    TReportThread.ProcessReportGenerationTask()    "Unexpected exception: The specified path, file name, or both are too long. The fully qualified file name must be less than 260 characters, and the directory name must be less than 248 characters"    Permission Scan_NHY_WIN_Bulk Import        17812    25976    45516
28/06/2024 23:05:29    INFO    SAJobEngine    TReportThread.Execute    "<- Work done"    Permission Scan_NHY_WIN_Bulk Import        17812    25976    45516
28/06/2024 23:05:29    INFO    SAJobEngine    TReportTaskExecute.ProcessReportTask    "Report generation and publishing task is done"    Permission Scan_NHY_WIN_Bulk Import        13080    25976    45516
28/06/2024 23:05:29    ERROR    SAJobEngine    TReportTaskExecute.ProcessReportTask    "Report generation task failed."    Permission Scan_NHY_WIN_Bulk Import        13080    25976    45516

------------------------------------------
"Unexpected exception: The specified path, file name, or both are too long. The fully qualified file name must be less than 260 characters, and the directory name must be less than 248 characters" error means that Windows cannot access the report file due to a long path to that report. You have to shrink the job name for Bulk Import jobs of both NHY and GLOBAL domains.

Regarding the "SQL logic error unknown database StrucMap" error for the NHY domain:


	Please make sure you have enough disk space on the drive where the StealthAUDIT is installed.
	Run the repair against ALNPIAF1201, SZE00-MS006, DESL2PV-EPO001, PHYDNAPSOV01, BRANAPV-PPDA01, NLANLPV-APP001 hosts of NHY domain. Follow the screenshot for the details. The repair might take some time so please wait for the completion. 



Please let us know the results once these checks are completed.

Best regards,

Aleksandr Timofeev
Technical Support Engineer EMEA

Regarding the "SQL logic error unknown database StrucMap" error for the NHY domain:


	Please make sure you have enough disk space on the drive where the StealthAUDIT is installed.

Can you set the Bulk Import to Debug mode and send us the log so we can review it?
To put the job on Debug mode, right-click on the job and click Properties.
Under the General tab, you will see the Log Level. If it is not already on Debug, click the dropdown and select it.

If the job was already on Debug, right-click on it and click Explore Folder. Open the OUTPUT folder, and you will see the FSAA Bulk Import_Log.tsv, which you can upload to this ticket.

If the job was not on Debug, you must put it on Debug, and you would need to rerun the job to collect the log before sending it to us.
